WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:03.769
[ Birds chirping ]

00:06.540 --> 00:12.410
♪♪

00:12.412 --> 00:14.947
So, I was able to find the keys.
[ Chuckles ]

00:14.949 --> 00:16.881
They were in the dishwasher
of all places.

00:16.883 --> 00:18.751
Turn on,
you piece of shit!

00:18.753 --> 00:21.954
So, uh, we don't usually
rent the place right
after the music festival

00:21.956 --> 00:23.155
'cause it takes me
a few days to clean up,

00:23.157 --> 00:25.023
but it was in
pretty good shape...

00:25.025 --> 00:26.891
except for a spill on the floor
that looked like,

00:26.893 --> 00:28.627
but certainly didn't taste like,
guacamole.

00:28.629 --> 00:30.094
Do you care
what card I use?

00:30.096 --> 00:31.430
Actually, it's my mother's
beach house,

00:31.432 --> 00:33.298
so if there's no paper trail,
then I can put this money

00:33.300 --> 00:37.435
right into my wedding fund,
so cash is king -- or queen.

00:37.437 --> 00:39.972
The cultural landscape's
shifting so fast, I don't
know what's right anymore.

00:39.974 --> 00:42.040
All right, there you go.
That's, uh --

00:42.042 --> 00:44.042
Look, do you have a phone
that I could borrow

00:44.044 --> 00:45.377
to call
technical support?

00:45.379 --> 00:47.579
I-I really have to get
this thing working.

00:47.581 --> 00:49.247
Sure.
You can use mine.

00:49.249 --> 00:52.050
♪♪

00:52.052 --> 00:53.986
Hey, um...

00:53.988 --> 00:56.721
still no results
from my paternity test?

00:56.723 --> 00:59.258
Nothing yet.
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

01:01.996 --> 01:05.397
But I was just about to go home
and check my mail.

01:05.399 --> 01:08.600
♪♪

01:08.602 --> 01:10.268
[ Ringing ]
Ugh.

01:10.270 --> 01:12.004
Hello, and welcome
to customer support.

01:12.006 --> 01:14.006
My name
is Jason Richardson,

01:14.008 --> 01:15.474
and I look forward
to helping you solve

01:15.476 --> 01:17.476
whatever problems
you are experiencing.

01:17.478 --> 01:19.411
May I ask who I have
the pleasure to be talking to?

01:19.413 --> 01:22.214
No. No, no, no. My
phone won't turn on.
That's all you need to know.

01:22.216 --> 01:25.217
I spent $1,000 on this thing
and it's a Goddamn...

01:25.219 --> 01:27.752
I'm going to Burger King.
You want anything?

01:27.754 --> 01:30.022
Well, as much as I would enjoy
a Masala Chicken Whopper,

01:30.024 --> 01:32.357
my wife has prepared
too much Mulligatawny soup.
Ah.

01:32.359 --> 01:35.928
That means, I carry the burden
of not letting it go to waste.

01:37.297 --> 01:40.165
...just the stupid thing
won't turn on!

01:40.167 --> 01:42.701
Yes, sir, I understand
that you are...

01:42.703 --> 01:43.836
distressed.

01:43.838 --> 01:45.838
I'm sure
I can help you today.

01:45.840 --> 01:48.841
Please tell me exactly what
problems you are experiencing?

01:48.843 --> 01:52.244
I just did!
Do you speak English?

01:52.246 --> 01:56.048
I do speak English.
Thank you for asking, sir.

01:56.050 --> 02:00.252
I...was...trying...
to...update...

02:00.254 --> 02:02.454
the...latest...
software...

02:02.456 --> 02:08.193
and...now...my...phone...
won't...turn...on.

02:08.195 --> 02:10.328
If I'm
understanding you, sir,

02:10.330 --> 02:14.933
you...were...trying...
to...update...

02:14.935 --> 02:16.935
the...latest...
software,

02:16.937 --> 02:22.074
and...now...your...phone...
won't...turn...on.
Bingo!

02:22.076 --> 02:24.676
Which means, I can't get my
photos, I can't get my videos,

02:24.678 --> 02:27.479
I can't get access to Facebook,
Instagram, Twitter...

02:27.481 --> 02:30.415
I'm done with the microwave
if you need to heat up

02:30.417 --> 02:33.151
your stinky soup.
Oh, thank you.
Is that a new blouse?

02:33.153 --> 02:35.420
I stole it
from my sister.

02:35.422 --> 02:38.423
...not to mention
Snapchat.

02:38.425 --> 02:40.759
Yes, sir, I am aware of all
the wonderful applications

02:40.761 --> 02:43.428
that are available to share
one's life experiences.
[ Sighs ]

02:43.430 --> 02:45.163
I'm going to talk
to my supervisor

02:45.165 --> 02:47.632
while I put you
on a brief hold.

02:47.634 --> 02:49.501
What?
No. No, no, n--

02:49.503 --> 02:51.570
Hey.
[ Snaps finger ]

02:51.572 --> 02:54.773
Hey, I got a cab waiting for
me outside and I don't want
to lose my place on hold.

02:54.775 --> 02:57.776
Um, can I maybe just borrow
your phone for a while?

02:57.778 --> 03:00.645
I'll, uh -- I'll swing you
an extra $20?
Yeah, why not?

03:00.647 --> 03:03.916
But if my podiatrist calls,
just tell him, "It's back."

03:03.918 --> 03:05.450
He'll know
what that means.

03:05.452 --> 03:12.725
♪♪

03:12.727 --> 03:16.661
<i> That's</i> why Nikki always leaves
the room whenever I'm around.

03:16.663 --> 03:18.931
She's freaked out
'cause I'm her baby's father.

03:18.933 --> 03:21.266
Oh! I thought
I just had bad breath.

03:21.268 --> 03:24.202
Holy shit.
I can stop flossing.
Mm-hmm.

03:24.204 --> 03:26.939
You need to figure out
what you're gonna do.
I know.

03:26.941 --> 03:29.007
My life is never gonna be
the same.

03:29.009 --> 03:31.410
Without flossing,
I can sleep in longer,

03:31.412 --> 03:33.278
my gums aren't gonna bleed
all the time,

03:33.280 --> 03:35.948
I won't have to keep cleaning
off my rearview mirror.

03:35.950 --> 03:37.549
Yeah, no, I was talking
about the baby.

03:37.551 --> 03:40.152
You know, once it grows muscles
and gets all hot,

03:40.154 --> 03:42.020
Tommy's gonna know
it isn't his.

03:42.022 --> 03:43.688
You gotta leave town.

03:43.690 --> 03:45.290
I can't just leave.

03:45.292 --> 03:48.226
I know moving to a new place
can seem scary,

03:48.228 --> 03:52.030
but that is why I am willing
to go with you.

03:52.032 --> 03:54.967
Look, I appreciate you
looking out for me,

03:54.969 --> 03:56.234
but I have a son now.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.637
I need to be around
in case he needs me.

03:58.639 --> 04:03.508
♪♪

04:03.510 --> 04:06.711
This might just be
the best day of my life.

04:06.713 --> 04:08.380
[ Chuckles ]

04:08.382 --> 04:11.850
[ Blowing ]

04:11.852 --> 04:18.056
♪♪

04:18.058 --> 04:20.525
Uh, you have someone
on hold.

04:20.527 --> 04:22.260
Oh, yes, I put him on hold
after Essha

04:22.262 --> 04:24.329
told me
the microwave was free.

04:24.331 --> 04:25.597
But when my soup
was reheating,

04:25.599 --> 04:28.733
Yashvi started going on and on
about his weekend plans.

04:28.735 --> 04:31.536
Next thing I knew,
I left my soup in too long.

04:31.538 --> 04:34.139
Well, it took a good bit
of blowing to get it cool enough

04:34.141 --> 04:36.074
to carry,
let alone to slurp.

04:36.076 --> 04:37.409
He's been on hold
for quite some time.

04:37.411 --> 04:39.011
Navdeep, you have
to pick that up.

04:39.013 --> 04:41.480
No, no, no.
He's going to be very mad.

04:41.482 --> 04:43.615
He's a spoiled brat
having a temper tantrum

04:43.617 --> 04:45.484
because he can't post
his food selfies

04:45.486 --> 04:47.686
and his basketball
trick shots.

04:47.688 --> 04:50.155
♪♪

04:50.157 --> 04:51.556
Hello, there, sir.

04:51.558 --> 04:53.291
[ Toilet flushes ]
No, I'm here! I'm here!

04:53.293 --> 04:56.361
Hello?
Just hold on!

04:56.363 --> 04:57.896
Yeah, no! Geez!
I'm here!
Are you there, sir?

04:57.898 --> 05:00.565
[ Grunts, groans ]

05:00.567 --> 05:03.702
Hello! Jason, I'm here!
I'm here.

05:03.704 --> 05:07.239
H-Hello, there, sir. My
name is Albert Anderson.
How many I help you?

05:07.241 --> 05:09.974
What do you mean "Albert"?
No, no, no. I was talking
to Jason Richardson.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.643
He -- He already knows
what's wrong.

05:11.645 --> 05:15.780
Uh, y-yes, sir, I-I understand
that you are...

05:15.782 --> 05:18.183
uh...perturbed.

05:18.185 --> 05:20.519
Uh, I am his supervisor,
and I'm here to ask you,

05:20.521 --> 05:22.254
in your own words,
if you would not mind,

05:22.256 --> 05:24.989
describing what problem
you're experiencing.

05:24.991 --> 05:26.791
I'm experiencing a phone
that doesn't work.

05:26.793 --> 05:29.261
I updated the software
on an airplane and --
[ Doorbell rings ]

05:29.263 --> 05:31.664
[ Cellphone buzzing ]
Uh, sir, I hate
to interrupt you,

05:31.666 --> 05:34.266
but I want to check our
system to see if this
is a common problem.

05:34.268 --> 05:35.800
What? No! I just --
Please hold.

05:35.802 --> 05:37.602
[ Buzzing continues ]

05:37.604 --> 05:40.873
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hi, Jasmine. I can't
talk right now. I'm working.

05:40.875 --> 05:42.675
It's time.

05:42.677 --> 05:44.510
Now?
Now.

05:46.613 --> 05:48.813
Okay, um...

05:48.815 --> 05:52.484
let me finish up here,
and, uh, I-I'll be right over.

05:52.486 --> 05:53.552
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:55.355 --> 05:57.222
...companies need to stop
putting their call centers

05:57.224 --> 05:59.224
in places where they can't
even figure out plumbing.

05:59.226 --> 06:00.893
I mean, this idiot is probably
putting me on hold

06:00.895 --> 06:04.429
to take a leak in the same river
where he's doing his dishes!

06:04.431 --> 06:06.565
I mean,
it's absolutely ins--

06:06.567 --> 06:08.300
[ Keys clacking ]

06:08.302 --> 06:10.102
What are you doing?

06:10.104 --> 06:12.237
Transferring this asshole
to my cellphone.

06:12.239 --> 06:14.038
Let's see just how
desperate he is

06:14.040 --> 06:16.308
to start getting likes again.
-...melting all the ice caps.

06:16.310 --> 06:17.576
-It's absolutely ins--
-Just a few more minutes, sir,

06:17.578 --> 06:19.511
and please remember
to stay on the line

06:19.513 --> 06:23.115
so we don't have
to start over.
No. D--

06:28.188 --> 06:31.123
[ Telephones ringing,
indistinct conversations ]

06:31.125 --> 06:32.958
[ Sighs ]

06:38.599 --> 06:39.864
[ Sighs ]

06:39.866 --> 06:41.333
Too cold.

06:43.770 --> 06:49.307
♪♪

06:49.309 --> 06:53.846
♪♪

06:53.848 --> 06:55.447
Who are you?

06:55.449 --> 06:57.716
Becky. Who are you?

06:57.718 --> 06:59.051
Vali.

07:00.387 --> 07:02.254
Hey.
Hey.

07:02.256 --> 07:03.788
Who is this?

07:03.790 --> 07:05.257
-Becky!
-Yep.

07:05.259 --> 07:07.659
I was babysitting at the hotel
when the nurse called.

07:07.661 --> 07:10.529
-Is the nurse here?
-She went to get the drugs.

07:10.531 --> 07:15.600
The, uh, medicine to make
Grandma feel better.

07:15.602 --> 07:18.937
-How's she feeling?
-She's in bed, but awake,

07:18.939 --> 07:21.005
if you want to spend
some time with her.

07:21.007 --> 07:22.207
She doesn't want to talk
about dying,

07:22.209 --> 07:24.209
so we've just been
playing board games.

07:24.211 --> 07:29.081
Oh, uh, she's a little too weak
for Hungry Hungry Hippos.

07:29.083 --> 07:31.216
So...

07:31.218 --> 07:33.085
this is really
happening, huh?

07:33.087 --> 07:34.753
She said she's ready.

07:34.755 --> 07:37.289
I tried to call Mom and
Dad, but they don't get
service on the ship.

07:37.291 --> 07:38.957
No, don't think
for one second the timing

07:38.959 --> 07:40.759
of their Alaskan cruise
was an accident.

07:40.761 --> 07:43.962
They knew this was coming.
They left this mess for us.

07:43.964 --> 07:45.430
Are you on a call?

07:45.432 --> 07:47.232
Uh, it's a work thing.

07:47.234 --> 07:50.435
Just some asshole
I'm making stay on hold.
Seriously?

07:50.437 --> 07:53.238
This prick can't get on
Facebook and thinks it's
the end of the world.

07:53.240 --> 07:55.373
Meanwhile, we're dealing
with life and death.

07:55.375 --> 07:57.710
Trust me,
he deserves it.

07:57.712 --> 07:59.444
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:59.446 --> 08:02.915
-Are you still there, sir?
-Yes, I'm still here, waiting.

08:02.917 --> 08:05.183
Where the hell
have you been?!

08:05.185 --> 08:08.520
Sir, I think perhaps your phone
took on some moisture.

08:08.522 --> 08:11.056
I'm going to need you
to find a bag of rice.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.657
I don't have
a bag of rice!

08:12.659 --> 08:15.127
I'm in a rental house!
Oh, that's fine.

08:15.129 --> 08:18.330
I'll keep you on hold while
you go to the grocery store...
[ Chuckles ]

08:18.332 --> 08:20.733
...and I will check in with you
periodically.

08:20.735 --> 08:22.601
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Aah!

08:22.603 --> 08:29.207
♪♪

08:29.209 --> 08:35.814
♪♪

08:35.816 --> 08:37.482
[ Cellphone beeps ]

08:37.484 --> 08:39.484
Hello, sir.

08:39.486 --> 08:42.621
No. W-- Uh, w-who is this?
Where's Albert Anderson?

08:42.623 --> 08:45.357
I've already explained
everything to Albert Anderson.

08:45.359 --> 08:48.827
My name is Angela Peterson in
specialized technical support,

08:48.829 --> 08:51.496
and I understand that you're
having some trouble today.

08:51.498 --> 08:54.299
Yeah. Okay, look, A-Albert
told me to go get some rice,

08:54.301 --> 08:56.701
so I'm almost
at the store.
Good.

08:56.703 --> 08:59.904
In the meantime, I need to get
some information from you.

08:59.906 --> 09:01.373
Could you read me
the serial number

09:01.375 --> 09:04.309
off the back of your phone?
-Back of the ph-- Um...

09:04.311 --> 09:07.312
Okay, yeah, it's,
um, "F," "V," 3 --

09:07.314 --> 09:10.783
I need you to say the
name of an animal when
you say the letters.

09:10.785 --> 09:13.051
Like, "F" is for fox.

09:13.053 --> 09:15.120
That way, I can understand
your accent.

09:15.122 --> 09:18.056
Y-- [ Scoffs ]
A-Are you kidding me?

09:18.058 --> 09:21.593
I...I think you said,
"Are you kidding me?"

09:21.595 --> 09:23.395
Uh, if that is
what you said, sir,

09:23.397 --> 09:27.132
then, uh, no, I am not
kidding with you.

09:27.134 --> 09:29.868
"F" as in fox.

09:29.870 --> 09:31.936
"V" as in --

09:31.938 --> 09:33.005
"V" as in --

09:33.007 --> 09:34.206
Damn it.
I can't think of an animal

09:34.208 --> 09:35.540
that starts
with the letter "V."

09:35.542 --> 09:38.811
-No problem. I can wait, sir.
-Ugh.

09:38.813 --> 09:41.079
♪♪

09:41.081 --> 09:42.614
What the hell
are you doing?

09:42.616 --> 09:46.018
Ugh, sweating my tits off
trying to eat this sausage.

09:46.020 --> 09:49.021
Seriously, Suzy, it's like
the devil farted on this thing.

09:49.023 --> 09:51.289
You asked for spicy,
you get spicy.

09:51.291 --> 09:54.493
Bodhi told me about the
baby and you trying to get
him to leave town with you.

09:54.495 --> 09:56.961
What are you up to?
I miss him, okay?

09:56.963 --> 09:58.430
It's all your fault.

09:58.432 --> 10:00.899
If you hadn't given him that
stupid-ass van to live in,

10:00.901 --> 10:02.100
we'd still be roommates.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.369
I thought you were turning
over a new leaf.

10:04.371 --> 10:07.105
Telling people's secrets,
meddling in people's lives --

10:07.107 --> 10:08.841
this feels more like
Tickles than Vivian.

10:08.843 --> 10:11.109
[ Mockingly ] "Feels more like
Tickles than Vivian."

10:11.111 --> 10:12.377
Shut up.
Just stay away from Bodhi

10:12.379 --> 10:13.912
before I tell him
the truth about you.

10:13.914 --> 10:16.181
Hey!
You say anything to Bodhi...

10:16.183 --> 10:19.718
[ Cellphone buzzes ]
...and I will stuff
your balls in your butt!

10:19.720 --> 10:21.654
Hey, get this --
Your stepmother just threatened

10:21.656 --> 10:24.857
to put my balls in my butt.
-Last digit is 3,

10:24.859 --> 10:26.925
as in, uh,
three turtle doves.

10:26.927 --> 10:28.393
Let me read that
back to you.

10:28.395 --> 10:31.996
I have "F" as in fox,
"V" as in vulture.

10:31.998 --> 10:34.733
[ Cellphone beeping ]
Shit. Shit.
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

10:34.735 --> 10:36.869
Uh, the phone I'm on
is about to run out of battery.

10:36.871 --> 10:38.270
Can you plug it in, sir?

10:38.272 --> 10:39.872
No, I don't have a charger
for it! It's not my phone!

10:39.874 --> 10:42.407
Oh, if you lose your place
in line, you'll have --

10:42.409 --> 10:45.944
Start all over again.
I know. I know!

10:45.946 --> 10:47.546
Put me on hold!

10:47.548 --> 10:50.749
♪♪

10:50.751 --> 10:54.419
[ Panting ]

10:54.421 --> 10:57.021
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:57.023 --> 10:58.757
Is your brother here?

10:58.759 --> 11:01.226
-He's in with her.
-Oh, all right.

11:01.228 --> 11:04.697
Well, this will more
than do the trick.

11:04.699 --> 11:08.100
♪♪

11:08.102 --> 11:10.435
Make sure you inject
all of it.

11:10.437 --> 11:12.504
What are you talking about?
I'm not doing it.

11:12.506 --> 11:14.839
[ Chuckling ]
I'm not doing it.

11:14.841 --> 11:18.711
She is asking for this.
It's the humane thing to do.

11:18.713 --> 11:20.178
Which is why

11:20.180 --> 11:23.115
I am<i> accidentally</i>
leaving this here

11:23.117 --> 11:26.585
for her family
to do the humane thing.

11:26.587 --> 11:29.288
No. No, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

11:30.057 --> 11:31.856
Who was that?
[ Door closes ]

11:31.858 --> 11:33.458
The nurse.

11:33.460 --> 11:36.461
Okay,
where did she go?

11:36.463 --> 11:38.196
Home.

11:38.198 --> 11:40.799
She says
we have to do it.

11:40.801 --> 11:43.535
♪♪

11:47.107 --> 11:48.507
I think this has already
been decided.

11:48.509 --> 11:51.109
We are not choosing
who k-k--

11:51.111 --> 11:53.245
gives Grandma
her medicine

11:53.247 --> 11:55.113
by whoever touches
their nose first.

11:55.115 --> 11:57.115
I d-- I didn't even know
that was a thing!

11:57.117 --> 11:59.518
Why don't you want
to give her her medicine?

11:59.520 --> 12:02.054
We are just a little afraid
of needles, that's all.

12:02.056 --> 12:04.589
Listen, if you're not going
to honor the nose thing,

12:04.591 --> 12:07.192
then we need to figure
something else out.
Rock, paper, scissors?

12:07.194 --> 12:08.793
A-And tell me how rock,
paper, scissors is not stupid?

12:08.795 --> 12:10.863
The nose thing doesn't
even have a name. That's
how stupid it is.

12:10.865 --> 12:12.997
In what world is
a sheet of paper stronger...
Hello?

12:12.999 --> 12:15.333
Uh, yeah -- yeah, hello.
W-Who is this?

12:15.335 --> 12:17.135
[ Arguing continues ]
Becky.

12:17.137 --> 12:20.405
Are you American? Please tell me
you're from America.

12:20.407 --> 12:21.740
-New Jersey.
-I'm sorry,

12:21.742 --> 12:24.543
just having a little trouble
hearing you.

12:24.545 --> 12:26.745
Be quiet!

12:26.747 --> 12:29.147
I'm on the phone.

12:29.149 --> 12:31.616
Becky? Hello?

12:31.618 --> 12:32.551
-Hey!
-Wh--

12:32.553 --> 12:34.619
Hello, sir.
Uh, are you still there?

12:34.621 --> 12:36.288
Yes, I'm here.
Put Becky back on.

12:36.290 --> 12:38.823
I want to talk to Becky.
-Oh, unfortunately,

12:38.825 --> 12:40.959
Becky is currently
assisting another customer,

12:40.961 --> 12:43.628
but I want you to know that
I'm concentrating on your case.

12:43.630 --> 12:45.163
Just hold a few more minutes.
-No, no, no.

12:45.165 --> 12:46.765
Don't put me back on hold.
-Thank you.

12:46.767 --> 12:48.032
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:48.034 --> 12:51.703
[ Muzak plays ]

12:51.705 --> 12:53.505
Another Blue Moon?

12:53.507 --> 12:54.907
Please.

12:58.178 --> 13:03.381
Hey, Vivian, how would you like
the entire weekend off with pay?

13:03.383 --> 13:04.649
[ Air hisses ]
Excuse me?

13:04.651 --> 13:06.518
Nikki's been pretty, uh,
stressed out lately,

13:06.520 --> 13:10.055
so I, uh, wanted to surprise her
with a romantic weekend,

13:10.057 --> 13:12.991
and I was wondering
if you would take Clark.

13:12.993 --> 13:15.193
You want to give me
your baby?

13:15.195 --> 13:17.329
Yeah, if you're cool with it.
I mean, he's super easy.

13:17.331 --> 13:19.264
You just have to feed him
and change him

13:19.266 --> 13:21.266
and keep him entertained
all day.

13:21.268 --> 13:23.668
I would love to take
your bab-- to babysit.

13:23.670 --> 13:25.003
I would love to babysit.

13:25.005 --> 13:26.671
Really?
Yeah.

13:26.673 --> 13:27.872
Oh, thank you.

13:27.874 --> 13:29.674
Okay, well, I will give you
the little guy tomorrow

13:29.676 --> 13:30.875
after your lunch shift.

13:30.877 --> 13:33.678
Can't wait.
[ Chuckles ]

13:33.680 --> 13:37.349
♪♪

13:37.351 --> 13:38.817
Not on my watch, Barbara.

13:38.819 --> 13:40.285
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

13:47.894 --> 13:50.829
[ Coughing ]

13:50.831 --> 13:53.766
Oh, man.
I missed it.

13:55.035 --> 13:58.036
Whoever knocks it over
does the deed.
Let's do it.

13:58.038 --> 14:04.977
♪♪

14:04.979 --> 14:12.116
♪♪

14:12.118 --> 14:19.057
♪♪

14:19.059 --> 14:20.592
[ Whispers ] Boom.

14:20.594 --> 14:28.667
♪♪

14:28.669 --> 14:36.741
♪♪

14:36.743 --> 14:44.683
♪♪

14:44.685 --> 14:52.757
♪♪

14:52.759 --> 15:00.833
♪♪

15:00.835 --> 15:03.002
[ Clattering ]

15:08.442 --> 15:12.044
Becky,
what did you do?

15:12.046 --> 15:14.446
I gave your grandma
her medicine.

15:14.448 --> 15:19.784
I'm not afraid of needles.
My brother is a diabetic.

15:19.786 --> 15:22.521
I bet you God will make her
better real soon.

15:22.523 --> 15:26.525
She was praying really fast
before she went to sleep.

15:26.527 --> 15:30.095
♪♪

15:37.571 --> 15:46.578
♪♪

15:46.580 --> 15:48.379
[ Door opens ]

15:48.381 --> 15:53.318
♪♪

15:53.320 --> 15:56.055
[ Door closes ]

15:56.057 --> 15:58.323
Did the coroner
come and get her?

15:58.325 --> 16:00.926
They did.

16:00.928 --> 16:02.594
I didn't know
whether or not to tip,

16:02.596 --> 16:06.665
so I did,
and then it felt weird.

16:06.667 --> 16:08.533
How's the little girl?

16:08.535 --> 16:09.735
Fine.

16:09.737 --> 16:11.070
Back with her family.

16:11.072 --> 16:13.872
Has no idea
she murdered someone.

16:13.874 --> 16:15.841
Hmm.

16:21.148 --> 16:24.149
Grandma was really
something, huh?

16:24.151 --> 16:26.952
Like no other.

16:26.954 --> 16:29.421
Oh, my God.
Remember her old neighbor?

16:29.423 --> 16:33.358
He would scream at me if my ball
even touched his grass,

16:33.360 --> 16:36.095
and then Grandma would
make me go over and mow
his lawn for free.

16:36.097 --> 16:38.964
[ Laughs ]
"Be kind to unkind people..."

16:38.966 --> 16:41.900
Together: "...because
they need it the most."

16:44.171 --> 16:45.370
Hmm.

16:45.372 --> 16:50.775
♪♪

16:50.777 --> 16:56.381
♪♪

16:56.383 --> 16:58.183
[ Cellphone beeps ]

16:58.185 --> 17:01.320
You still there, man?
Yeah, still here.

17:01.322 --> 17:02.921
What?

17:02.923 --> 17:07.058
Okay, press the power button
and the two volume buttons

17:07.060 --> 17:08.927
at the same time
for 20 seconds.

17:08.929 --> 17:12.731
Then what?
Put it in a bucket of chicken?

17:12.733 --> 17:14.333
Then it'll come back on.

17:14.335 --> 17:16.601
Real-- Really?
That's -- That's it?

17:16.603 --> 17:18.870
That's it.
[ Laughs ]

17:18.872 --> 17:20.739
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, my God.

17:20.741 --> 17:23.875
You saved me.
Thank you so much.

17:23.877 --> 17:26.011
You're welcome.

17:26.013 --> 17:29.548
And I'm sorry it took
me so long to realize
the right thing to do.

17:29.550 --> 17:32.551
Oh, my God!
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:32.553 --> 17:36.421
Oh, Albert Anderson!
Yeah!

17:36.423 --> 17:41.693
♪♪

17:41.695 --> 17:43.762
And I was really struggling

17:43.764 --> 17:46.898
with the right words
to say today,

17:46.900 --> 17:49.701
but then I remembered
that a picture

17:49.703 --> 17:51.102
is worth a thousand words,

17:51.104 --> 17:56.241
and thanks to Facebook,
Instagram, and Snapchat,

17:56.243 --> 17:57.776
I've realized
I had everything I needed --

17:57.778 --> 17:59.444
Well, almost everything.

17:59.446 --> 18:02.981
I had a bit of a glitch
with my phone earlier today,

18:02.983 --> 18:05.851
and I freaked out on some people
in India for a while.

18:05.853 --> 18:07.586
[ Laughter ]

18:07.588 --> 18:11.390
But, um...even though, uh,

18:11.392 --> 18:14.994
I was being a jerk,
they helped me.

18:14.996 --> 18:18.197
And thanks to one
very nice gentleman,

18:18.199 --> 18:20.932
I give you...

18:20.934 --> 18:23.402
my grandmother.

18:23.404 --> 18:25.136
She was like no other.

18:25.138 --> 18:29.474
♪♪

18:29.476 --> 18:32.343
♪ My grandmother
was like no other ♪

18:32.345 --> 18:34.413
[ Telephone rings ]
♪ Too bad you didn't meet her ♪

18:34.415 --> 18:37.082
♪ Every day at 3:00,
she'd have G and T ♪

18:37.084 --> 18:39.484
♪ At bridge
you could not beat her ♪

18:39.486 --> 18:42.087
♪ Christmastime
she'd end up crying ♪

18:42.089 --> 18:45.490
♪ Listening to Chevalier ♪

18:45.492 --> 18:47.826
♪ And I got 10 bucks
and a card each year ♪

18:47.828 --> 18:50.829
♪ In September for my birthday ♪

18:54.235 --> 18:56.702
♪ My grandmother
didn't much bother ♪

18:56.704 --> 18:58.770
♪ Too much about
being a granny ♪

18:58.772 --> 19:01.773
♪ She didn't bake or knit,
she didn't give a shit ♪

19:01.775 --> 19:03.842
♪ Us kids called her nanny ♪

19:03.844 --> 19:06.645
♪ In the summertime,
we'd visit her ♪

19:06.647 --> 19:10.249
♪ Take the train
to Rhode Island ♪

19:10.251 --> 19:12.383
♪ Westerly all east taxi ♪

19:12.385 --> 19:15.120
♪ Would pick us up
and we'd all pile in ♪

19:18.792 --> 19:21.192
♪ My grandmother,
my sister, and my brother ♪

19:21.194 --> 19:23.394
♪ And me all went to the ocean ♪

19:23.396 --> 19:26.065
♪ In her cabana there
in a big beach chair ♪

19:26.067 --> 19:28.399
♪ She'd survey our commotion ♪

19:28.401 --> 19:30.802
♪ At the yacht club,
we'd get our grub ♪

19:30.804 --> 19:34.606
♪ We had grinders
and grape sodas ♪

19:34.608 --> 19:36.942
♪ What a dream --
popcorn, ice cream ♪

19:36.944 --> 19:39.445
♪ Two weeks,
no junk-food quotas ♪

19:43.416 --> 19:45.284
♪ My grandmother
would light up another ♪

19:45.286 --> 19:48.219
♪ You know that cough of hers
was chronic ♪

19:48.221 --> 19:50.355
♪ She didn't drink wine,
but she was just fine ♪

19:50.357 --> 19:53.092
♪ With a nice tall
gin and tonic ♪

19:53.094 --> 19:55.627
♪ Nanny had opinions ♪

19:55.629 --> 19:59.164
♪ Nanny wasn't prissy ♪

19:59.166 --> 20:01.300
♪ She took us in
despite our sins ♪

20:01.302 --> 20:03.969
♪ Gave us cover
when things got tricky ♪

20:07.574 --> 20:10.309
♪ My grandmother
was like no other ♪

20:10.311 --> 20:12.311
♪ Too bad you didn't meet her ♪

20:12.313 --> 20:14.913
♪ Every day at 3:00,
she'd have G and T ♪

20:14.915 --> 20:17.516
♪ At bridge
you could not beat her ♪

20:17.518 --> 20:20.119
♪ Christmastime
she'd end up crying ♪

20:20.121 --> 20:23.322
♪ Listening to
Maurice Chevalier ♪

20:23.324 --> 20:26.057
♪ And I got 10 bucks
and a card each year ♪

20:26.059 --> 20:27.726
♪ In September for my birthday ♪

20:27.728 --> 20:30.595
Nikki wants you
to have the baby.
What?

20:30.597 --> 20:33.665
Yeah, she told Tommy
you were the father.
They had a huge fight.

20:33.667 --> 20:36.935
Oh, no. Is Tommy pissed?
He's pissed, isn't he?

20:36.937 --> 20:38.870
Furious!
You gotta leave town.

20:38.872 --> 20:40.205
With the baby?

20:40.207 --> 20:41.740
I don't know anything
about babies.

20:41.742 --> 20:43.408
Don't worry.
I'm gonna help you.

20:43.410 --> 20:45.144
Look, God doesn't give out
breasts like these

20:45.146 --> 20:47.012
without some natural
mothering instincts.

20:47.014 --> 20:48.147
We -- We have to leave
right now?

20:48.149 --> 20:49.614
Can I at least say goodbye
to Eddie?

20:49.616 --> 20:51.016
No. We don't have time.

20:51.018 --> 20:52.351
Besides,
I think I heard him say

20:52.353 --> 20:53.885
something about
leaving town himself.

20:53.887 --> 20:56.888
He didn't say goodbye to you.
So rude.

20:56.890 --> 21:00.025
♪♪
